article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 69, St. Francis, N.Y. 60
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- John Bunch had 11 points, 11 rebounds and 10 blocked shots to lead Monmouth to a 69-60 win over St. Francis of New York on Saturday night. Jhamar Youngblood added 19 points and Whitney Coleman had 17 points for the Hawks (10-12, 5-5 in Northeast Conference). Robert Hines had a game-high 20 points and eight rebounds to lead the Terriers (5-19, 3-9), while John Gooden added 15 points and Allan Sheppard chipped in with 14 points. Monmouth led for most of the game and held several double-digit leads, but they had trouble putting away St. Francis, which tried to rally late. However, the Terriers could not get closer than seven points in the closing minutes, and Monmouth sealed the win by going 6-for-9 from the free throw line in the final minute.
